          </div>
          <div class="accordion-content accordion-content-faq" style="display: block;" data-accordion-id="faq-payment" data-accordion-group="faq">
            <p>Personal data means any information about you which is personally identifiable, including, without limitation, your name, address, telephone number, email address, financial details, registration name, password and other information from which you can be identified and which you disclose to us at any time.</p>
            <br>
          </div>
          <div class="ordering-faq cgv-bg accordion accordion-faq active" data-accordion-href="faq-contract" data-accordion-group="faq">
            <h2 class="block-title-faq">2. COLLECTION OF YOUR PERSONAL DATA</h2>
            <div class="spacer-faq-title">&nbsp;</div>
            <p class="view-details-faq"><span class="btn-plus btn-plus-faq"><span class="open">view details</span> <span class="close">Close</span> </span></p>
            <br>
          </div>
          <div class="accordion-content accordion-content-faq" style="display: block;" data-accordion-id="faq-contract" data-accordion-group="faq">
            <p>We collect your Personal Data when:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>• you create an online account ("Account");</li>
              <li>• you place an order via the Website or by telephone;</li>
              <li>• you subscribe to the Lacoste’s newsletter</li>
              <li>• you make a complaint or enquiry or provide other feedback to us; and</li>
              <li>• you disclose your Personal Data to us through the Website or at any other point (including Lacoste stores).</li>
            </ul>
            <p>The information that you provide when setting up your account or making a purchase from the online store may include your name, email address, telephone number, delivery address, billing address and payment information. Please note that we will not be storing your payment information, this will be done via a third party payments company. If you register to hold an account with us, you will also have a unique password which enables you to access your account.<br>The information that you provide when setting up your account or making a purchase from the online store may include your name, email address, telephone number, delivery address, billing address and payment information. Please note that we will not be storing your payment information, this will be done via a third party payments company. If you register to hold an account with us, you will also have a unique password which enables you to access your account.<br>Where permitted by law, we may combine this information we receive from other sources, including from social media websites, with information you give to us and information we collect about you. We may use this information and the combined information for learning more about your preferences as our customer, for enhancing your user experience on our websites and for providing you with information, content and offerings tailored to your needs. In addition, we use cookies as explained in section 9 below.<br>Where collection of some personal data is necessary for us to carry out the purposes listed in section 3 below, we will make it clear that we will not be able to carry out those purposes without provision of the information.</p>
            <br>
          </div>
          <div class="ordering-faq cgv-bg accordion accordion-faq active" data-accordion-href="faq-account" data-accordion-group="faq">
            <h2 class="block-title-faq">3. USE OF YOUR PERSONAL DATA</h2>
